hackathon-description-text: CalgaryHacks is a hackathon hosted by the University of Calgary’s Computer Science Undergraduate Society. Students in teams of up to five will be able to work with the latest technologies to build amazing projects.
hackathon-rules:
-Teams of up to five
-24 hours to create a hack
-Projects cannot be started until the hacking officially begins
-Must follow the MLH code of conduct, located on our official website.

hackathon-prizes.prize-content: Robot kits for the whole team

hackathon-location-google-maps: https://maps.google.com/?q=856 Campus Pl NW, Calgary, AB T2N 4V8, Canada

hackathon-judging-criteria.judging-criterion: Innovation, User Interface/User Experience, Overall Quality, Quality of Pitch, Relation to Theme
